# Content updates

When editing portfolio content:

1. Change data in `content/*.ts`, not in section components.
2. Experience entries: newest job first in `content/experience.ts`.
3. Each experience needs: `role`, `company`, `companyLink`, `period`, `bullets`.
4. Use `achievements` for measurable outcomes (coverage %, cost reduction, latency).
5. Certifications go in `content/certifications.ts`.
6. Header title and bio → `content/profile.ts` (`profile.title`, `profile.bio`).
7. How I Work principles → `content/how-i-work.ts`.
8. Blog articles → `content/articles/*.md` with frontmatter (`published: true` to go live).
9. Blog production flag → `content/features.ts` (`enabledInProduction`).
10. Blog index copy → `content/blog.ts`.
11. See `docs/CONTENT.md` for full reference.
